body_html:
@EdeMeijer your solution worked for my VGG16 graph: https://gist.github.com/eggie5/7d9c31c08462ec42ed8d927f2c0c3e55

import tensorflow as tf
dir(tf.contrib) #hack per https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/10130
with tf.Session() as sess:  
    tf.saved_model.loader.load(sess, [tf.saved_model.tag_constants.SERVING], 'model/export/1509295446/')
    print [n.name for n in tf.get_default_graph().as_graph_def().node]

Before I was getting that same error as you.
